nt & The Shakedown<ref name=\"AC/DC Tour Archive\"/>\n|12,320 / 13,898\n|$1,268,400\n|-\n|30 August 2016\n|[[Sunrise, Florida|Sunrise]]\n|[[BB&T Center (Sunrise, Florida)|BB&T Center]]\n|11,930 / 12,944\n|$1,263,029\n|-\n|1 September 2016\n|[[Atlanta]]\n|[[State Farm Arena|Philips Arena]]\n| 11,173 / 13,012\n|$1,169,355\n|-\n|4 September 2016\n|[[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]]\n|[[Nationwide Arena]]\n|11,032 / 15,771\n|$1,366,460\n|-\n|6 September 2016\n|[[Cleveland]]\n|[[Quicken Loans Arena]]\n|8,355 / 9,113\n|$901,870\n|-\n|9 September 2016\n|[[Auburn Hills, Michigan|Auburn Hills]]\n|[[The Palace of Auburn Hills]]\n|7,897 / 12,626\n|$904,984\n|-\n|11 September 2016\n|[[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]]\n|[[KeyBank Center]]\n| 10,000 / 14,000\n| \u2014\n|-\n|14 September 2016\n|[[New York City]]\n|[[Madison Square Garden]]\n|13,737 / 13,737\n|$1,555,320\n|-\n|17 September 2016\n|[[Washington, D.C.]]\n|[[Capital One Arena|Verizon Center]]\n|11,708 / 14,182\n|$1,423,688\n|-\n|20 September 2016\n|[[Philadelphia]]\n|[[Wells Fargo Center (Philadelphia)|Wells Fargo Center]]\n|14,089 / 14,089\n|$1,216,141\n|-\n! colspan=\"5\" | '''Total'''\n!\n!$221,100,000\n|}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Angus Young]] \u2013 [[lead guitar]]\n*[[Cliff Williams]] \u2013 [[bass guitar]], [[backing vocals]]\n*[[Stevie Young]] \u2013 [[rhythm guitar]], backing vocals\n*[[Chris Slade]] \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]]\n*[[Brian Johnson]] \u2013 [[lead vocals]] (Legs 1-5)\n*[[Axl Rose]] \u2013 lead vocals (Legs 6-7)\n\n==Grossing==\nThe Rock or Bust Tour was the second most attended tour of 2015 behind [[One Direction]] and third highest-grossing tour behind [[Taylor Swift]] and One Direction (Pollstar Year End Top 100 Worldwide tours of 2015).\nThe tour grossed $180&nbsp;million from 54 shows in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pollstarpro.com/files/charts2015/2015YearEndTop100WorldwideTours.pdf |title = Pollstar &#124; Welcome to the New Pollstar!}}</ref> and $40.1&nbsp;million from 32 shows in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.pollstarpro.com/files/charts2016/2016YearEndTop100WorldwideTours.pdf |title = Pollstar &#124; Welcome to the New Pollstar!}}</ref> Total gross: $221.1&nbsp;million from 86 shows performed.\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|group=\"nb\"}}\n\n{{AC/DC}}\n\n[[Category:AC/DC concert tours]]\n[[Category:2015 concert tours]]\n[[Category:2016 concert tours]]\n[[Category:Axl Rose]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Concert tour by Australian rock band AC/DC}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox concert tour\n| image         = File:Rock_Or_Bust_World_Tour_Promo_Poster.jpg\n| image_size    = 300px\n| image_caption = Rock or Bust World Tour Promo Poster\n| border        = yes\n| location          \n| artist          = [[AC/DC]]\n| album           = ''[[Rock or Bust]]''\n| start_date      = 10 April 2015\n| end_date        = 20 September 2016\n| number_of_legs  = 7\n| number_of_shows = {{unbulleted list|41 in Europe|36 in North America|11 in Oceania|88 total <ref name=\"themusic.com.au\">{{cite web|url=http://themusic.com.au/news/all/2016/03/08/doctors-tell-acdc-frontman-brian-johnson-to-stop-touring-immediately/|title=Doctors Tell AC/DC Frontman Brian Johnson To Stop Touring Immediately|work=theMusic|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref>}}\n| gross           = $221.1 million\n| last_tour       = [[Black Ice World Tour]]<br>(2008-10)\n| this_tour       = '''Rock or Bust World Tour'''<br>(2015-16)\n}}\n\n'''Rock or Bust World Tour''' was a 2015\u20132016 [[concert tour]] by Australian [[rock music|rock]] band [[AC/DC]], in support of their sixteenth  studio album ''[[Rock or Bust]]'' (2014).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news/acdc-first-2015-european-tour-dates-revealed/|title=Ac/Dc: First 2015 European Tour Dates Announced - Blabbermouth.net|work=BLABBERMOUTH.NET|accessdate=18 April 2016|date=12 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ac-dc.net/archives/subcategory.php?subcategory_id=125|title=AC/DC The Archives|accessdate=18 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927165015/http://www.ac-dc.net/archives/subcategory.php?subcategory_id=125|archive-date=27 September 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/sep/24/acdc-confirm-departure-of-malcolm-young-new-album-rock-or-bust|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140924153656/http://www.theguardian.com/music/2014/sep/24/acdc-confirm-departure-of-malcolm-young-new-album-rock-or-bust|title=AC/DC's Malcolm Young departs as new album Rock or Bust announced|author=Guardian music|archivedate=24 September 2014|newspaper=the Guardian|accessdate=18 April 2016|date=24 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vividseats.com/blog/acdc-tour-2015-confirmed-for-north-american-stadiums |title=AC/DC Tour 2015 Confirmed for North American Stadiums |accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nOpening on 10 April 2015, at [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]] in [[Indio, California]].\n\n[[Malcolm Young]] was replaced by his and Angus' nephew [[Stevie Young]] and [[Phil Rudd]] was replaced by their former drummer [[Chris Slade]]. They have both played for AC/DC on the [[Blow Up Your Video World Tour]] and on the [[Razors Edge World Tour]], respectively.\n\nIn Germany, the band set a new world record in the number of sold tickets within the shortest timespan, with more than 300,000 tickets sold out in seventy-seven minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vorverkaufstarts.de/acdc-tour-tickets|title=AC/DC Tour 2015 / 2016 {{!}} Tickets|date=12 December 2014|website=Vorverkaufstarts.de|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045829/http://www.vorverkaufstarts.de/acdc-tour-tickets|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead|access-date=2 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn Switzerland, the band set a new record in the duration to a 'sold out' concert. The concert in Zurich was sold out in 6 minutes (over 40,000 tickets) <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blick.ch/people-tv/musik/ausverkauft-nach-6-minuten-ac-dc-brechen-den-allzeit-rekord-id3351118.html|title=Ausverkauft nach 6 Minuten: AC/DC brechen den Allzeit-Rekord!|author=Blick|date=16 December 2014|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe band played at the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards]], performing \"[[Rock or Bust (song)|Rock or Bust]]\" and \"[[Highway to Hell]]\" on 8 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/news/ariana-grande-madonna-among-first-57th-grammy-performers|title=Ariana Grande, Madonna Among First 57th GRAMMY Performers|work=The GRAMMYs|accessdate=18 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe last 22 shows were rescheduled as [[Brian Johnson]] was ordered to stop touring immediately.<ref name=\"themusic.com.au\"/> Ten shows from 8 March 2016 to 4 April 2016 were cancelled and had to be rescheduled,<ref name=\"acdc.com Ten US Tour dates rescheduled\">{{cite web |url=http://www.acdc.com/news?n_id=274 |title=AC/DC to reschedule Upcoming U.S. Tour dates |date= 7 March 2016 |website=acdc.com |accessdate= 17 April 2016}}</ref> with [[Axl Rose]] of [[Guns N' Roses]] appearing in Johnson's place <ref name=\"acdc.com Rock or Bust World Tour resumes with Axl Rose on vocals\">{{cite web |url=http://www.acdc.com/news?n_id=278 |title=Rock Or Bust World Tour Continues With Axl Rose |date= 16 April 2016 |website=acdc.com |accessdate= 17 April 2016}}</ref> marking first time that AC/DC has featured a lead vocalist other than Brian Johnson since they concluded the [[Highway to Hell Tour]] on 27 January 1980.\n\nAs part of this tour, AC/DC performed the first concert at the [[Olympic Stadium (London)|Olympic Stadium]] in London since its redevelopment following the 2012 Olympic and Paralympic Games.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nme.com/news/acdc--2/93981 | title=Axl Rose and AC/DC play first ever concert at London's Olympic Stadium | publisher=NME | date=5 June 2016 | accessdate=5 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nLongtime bassist [[Cliff Williams]] announced that he would retire upon completion of the tour, citing losing interest following the health issues with Malcolm Young and Brian Johnson, and the legal issues with Phil Rudd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gulfshorelife.com/July-2016/Still-Rockin-in-Southwest-Florida-ACDC-Cliff-Williams-Brian-Howe-Steve-Luongo/|title=Still Rockin' in Southwest Florida|work=Gulfshore Life|first=Jonathan|last=Foerste|accessdate=8 September 2016|date=July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170612011918/http://www.gulfshorelife.com/July-2016/Still-Rockin-in-Southwest-Florida-ACDC-Cliff-Williams-Brian-Howe-Steve-Luongo/|archive-date=12 June 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nThe band broke their normal routine at the end of the final concert with Angus Young leading Williams out to the front of the stage to take a final bow. Rose also introduced the band members one by one.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ultimateclassicrock.com/ac-dc-rock-or-bust-last-show/|title=AC/DC Play Last 'Rock or Bust' Show in Philadelphia: Photos, Set List, Review|website=Ultimate Classic Rock}}</ref>\n\n==Setlist==\n[[File:ACDC Tacoma WA Feb 2 2016.jpg|right|300px|thumb|AC/DC performing in [[Tacoma, Washington]] on Feb. 2, 2016.]]\n[[File:AC DC at London's Olympic Stadium.jpg|right|300px|thumb|AC/DC with Axl Rose performing the first concert at the [[Olympic Stadium (London)|Olympic Stadium]] in London, on June 4, 2016.]]\n# \"[[Rock or Bust (song)|Rock or Bust]]\"\n# \"[[Shoot to Thrill]]\"\n# \"Hell Ain't a Bad Place to Be\"\n# \"[[Back in Black (song)|Back in Black]]\"\n# \"[[Play Ball (song)|Play Ball]]\" \n# \"Got Some Rock & Roll Thunder\"\n# \"[[Dirty Deeds Done Dirt Cheap (song)|Dirty Deeds Done Dirt Cheap]]\"\n# \"[[Rock 'n' Roll Damnation]]\"\n# \"[[Thunderstruck (song)|Thunderstruck]]\"\n# \"[[High Voltage (song)|High Voltage]]\"\n# \"[[Rock N Roll Train]]\"\n# \"[[Hells Bells (song)|Hells Bells]]\"\n# \"Baptism by Fire\" \n# \"[[Dog Eat Dog (AC/DC song)|Dog Eat Dog]]\"\n# \"If You Want Blood (You've Got It)\"\n# \"[[Touch Too Much]]\"\n# \"Live Wire\"\n# \"[[You Shook Me All Night Long]]\"\n# \"Sin City\"\n# \"Shot Down in Flames\"\n# \"Have a Drink on Me\"\n# \"[[T.N.T. (song)|T.N.T.]]\"\n# \"[[Whole Lotta Rosie]]\"\n# \"[[Let There Be Rock (song)|Let There Be Rock]]\" <small>(including Angus Young's guitar solo)</small>\n'''Encore'''\n# <li value=25>\"[[Highway to Hell (song)|Highway to Hell]]\"\n#\"[[Riff Raff (song)|Riff Raff]]\"\n#\"[[Problem Child (AC/DC song)|Problem Child]]\"\n#\"[[For Those About to Rock (We Salute You)]]\"\n\nNote: \"Sin City\" played before \"You Shook Me All Night Long\" on 2016 shows. \"Got Some Rock & Roll Thunder\" and \"Givin' the Dog a Bone\" only played on 2016 shows.<ref>{{Cite web|title = AC/DC Average Setlists of year: 2016 {{!}} setlist.fm|url = http://www.setlist.fm/stats/average-setlist/acdc-23d6807b.html?year=2016|website = www.setlist.fm|access-date = 2016-02-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = AC/DC Average Setlists of year: 2015 {{!}} setlist.fm|url = http://www.setlist.fm/stats/average-setlist/acdc-23d6807b.html?year=2015|website = www.setlist.fm|access-date = 2016-02-20}}</ref>\n\n==Coachella Set list==\n{{hidden\n| headercss = background: #CECEF2; font-size: 100%; width: 100%;\n| contentcss = text-align: left; font-size: 100%; width: 95%;\n| header = Coachella Set List \n| content =\n# \"Hell Ain't a Bad Place to Be\"\n# \"Shot Down in Flames\"\n# \"[[Back in Black (song)|Back in Black]]\"\n# \"[[Rock or Bust (song)|Rock or Bust]]\"\n# \"[[Shoot to Thrill]]\"\n# \"[[Dirty Deeds Done Dirt Cheap (song)|Dirty Deeds Done Dirt Cheap]]\"\n# \"[[Thunderstruck (song)|Thunderstruck]]\"\n# \"[[Play Ball (song)|Play Ball]]\" \n# \"The Jack\" \n# \"[[High Voltage (song)|High Voltage]]\"\n# \"[[Hells Bells (song)|Hells Bells]]\"\n# \"Baptism by Fire\"\n# \"[[You Shook Me All Night Long]]\"\n# \"Have a Drink on Me\"\n# \"Sin City\"\n# \"[[T.N.T. (song)|T.N.T.]]\"\n# \"[[Rock 'N Roll Train]]\